PARIS HAWAII (Paris-Hawaii) is a French restaurant that creates high-quality food grown in Hawaii's rich nature using traditional French techniques  The executive chef is Yuya Yamanaka (Satoshi Yamanaka), who worked as a sous chef at the long-established bistro "Le Crown Bar" in Paris, France.  After moving to Hawaii in 2015 and facing Hawaii's food culture, producers and ingredients for three years, he brings out the charm of Hawaiian materials with French techniques and creativity cultivated in Paris. Healthy and surprisingly very earthy and delicious. )  Next came garlic shrimp,  then the tako dish,  Opah, Maui onion soup,  chicken,  and last of the main courses,  the Big Island Beef dish ❤.   I love, love the gastronomical adventure that they presented.   The menu changes every few months.   The service was like clockwork,  perfect.   The Chefs Table afforded us the view of every single dish prepared.  I can keep on gushing about the food,  but it will not do it justice.   So I will leave it be.  Oh, ...just one last thing.   The last tea pairing was a chocolate ( infused?) tea.  This,  I can just smell all day.   The scent was heavenly to say the least.   I don't even need to taste it and I'd be happy.  Overall, the farm to table concept definitely works here.

(Translated by Google) Of course, the combination of ingredients, dishes, serving, atmosphere of the shop, all of them enjoyed, not to mention the taste! Recommend the seat in front of the eyes where the chef's work can be seen.  (Original) お味は勿論、素材の組み合わせ、食器、盛り付け、お店の雰囲気、全て満喫しました!! シェフの仕事が見える目の前のお席がオススメ。

We decided to come here because of a glowing review from the Honolulu Magazine. I called in to reserve 2 seats at the Chef's Table and was confirmed. However, when we showed up, we were led to a regular table and when questioned, we were told that the Chef's Table was already full. This was quite disappointing as we wanted to the chef in action. Confusingly, a few minutes later, we were taken back to the Chef's Table. There was no apology nor explanation.  The food here was good and I absolutely LOVED the tea pairings! I have never seen that offered before and my girlfriend and I are not huge alcohol drinkers. The teas offered were unique and refreshing. I was told that they were all made from local ingredients. It ranged from a kombucha tea to a hot chocolate tea! I very much enjoyed it and I hope to see more places offer tea pairings.  Our favorite dish from the prix fixe menu was the PARIS Poke. I am usually skeptical on alternate takes on poke, but this was absolutely incredible. The smoothest ahi poke seasoned just right with shoyu sits over a poached egg. It is all topped with a Big Island beef tartare. The flavors of the egg, ahi, and beef blend oh so well and the textures! The textures in one spoonful of that dish just amazing.  The only other issue we had was with the service. Not all of the dishes were explained to us. In the beginning, they were explained very well, but near the middle and the end we were just served the dish without much interaction from the servers or the chefs. At the chefs table, we were hoping for more of an interactive experience.  They validate 4 hours worth of parking at the Hyatt Centric located a short walk away. This was very appreciated as parking in Waikiki is always difficult and/or expensive
Pre-fixe menu, absolutely fabulous! We had two wine pairings with each course(8) and two desserts, plus 2 cocktails, 2 coffees. Final bill $360 ish. So worth it!!! Thank you PARIS HAWAII!!!
A fresh place to go for a relax and break for tasty drinks made from local ingredients and local spirits 🍹🍸 Just new, it's worth checking out for a change!
